  "title": "Utility Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p>1.   Plan, schedule and manage of all aspect of utilities coordination related works.</p><p>2.   Coordinate and communicate with various stakeholders, including but not limited to design consultants/engineers, other departments, project representatives from clients, statutory / authority agencies, etc., to set the requirements for work deliverables and engineering works that must be submitted.</p><p>3.   Manage and monitor progress, quality of workmanship and ensure that it complies with authority requirements.</p><p>4.   Highlight any discrepancies and advise the staff on the interfacing of utility services and related works.</p><p>5.   Coordination with other disciplines to guarantee that designs meet other infrastructure requirements.</p><p>6.   Perform all duties in accordance with company policies, processes, systems, and procedures.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>1.   Minimum Degree in Mechanical or Civil Engineer with at least 3 years of underground utilities matter.</p><p>2.    LTA Project Experience is preferred</p>",
